The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           IN THE CITY
                  
	 Alexander Satschko of Germany beat David Savic of Serbia 6-3, 6-4 to lift the ITF-Futures meet title at the Jaidip Mukerjea Tennis Academy on Saturday. He takes home $1950.           
	 Karnataka emerged champions in the BHA centenary 6-a-side Indoor hockey tournament beating Punjab 4-2 at the Netaji Indoor Stadium on Saturday. In an exhibition match, Mohun Bagan were held 1-1 by archrivals East Bengal while Bengal (Red) defeated Bengal (White) 2-0 in the womens exhibition tie. Ravi Kumar and Dhanwinder Singh were adjudged best player and goalkeeper respectively.          
	 Calcutta Rowing Club (CRC) emerged overall champions in the First International Friendship Regatta at the Calcutta Rowing Club on Saturday.                 
	CRICKET: Ranji Trophy Plate Group B match  Bengal vs Tripura at the Eden from 9am                                                                                                                                                                     
